name: seal_jacks1.gif
info: Seal jacks is cardiovascular exercise that primarily targets shoulders, upper chest, quads and calves.
howTo: Stand straight with your feets together and arms extended in front of your chest. Jump in air spreading out your legs and closing your arms at same time. Jump back to start and repeat the movement.
correctForm:
Keep your arms & back straight
Arms should go out wide

name: torso_rotation1.gif
info: Torso rotation engages your core body muscles that primarily includes your abs and back.
howTo: Stand upright with holding both hands together. Rotate your torso out at one side while placing your hands on top of each other. Then rotate back to opposite direction. This completes one repetition.
correctForm:
Keep lower body static
Keep feets at shoulder width part

name: cobra_stretch.gif
info: Cobra stretch helps strengthening muscles of arms, shoulders, chest and abdominals.
howTo: Lie face down on the floor with parallel thigh placement and place your hands underneath your shoulders. Start straightening your arms with chest lift and maintain a comfortable height of torso. Relax and hold the stretch upwards.
correctForm:
Tit head back and look upkeep
Keep your abs and back relaxed

name: shoulder_stretch
info: Shoulder and back stretch is an effective exercise that treats neck and shoulder pain. It also improves circulation in the shoulder joint and muscles.
howTo: Stand straight while keeping your head up and raise arms straight up over your body and hold both hands together. Slowly stretch your torso towards right side of your body and hold on for couple of seconds. Then stretch torso towards left side of your body and then come back to starting position.
correctForm:
Exhale as you deepen the stretch, breath in as you release the stretch
Keep shoulders in neutral position

name: side_bend_stretch1.gif
info: Side bend stretch is an effective exercise that primarily targets obliques, abs and back.
howTo: Stand straight with your feet shoulder width apart, place right hand on your side hip and raise the left arm straight up over the body. Incline your upper body to the right side and hold the stretch then repeat on the other side.
correctForm:
Bend your torso slowly without moving hips
Distribute weight of your upper body evenly between both legs

name: cat_cow_stretch.gif
info: Cat cow stretch is core exercise that brings flexibility to the spine. It helps relieving back pain.
howTo: Get down on the floor with your hands and knees in a view aligning your palms underneath shoulders and knees underneath hips. Curl your toes under, inhale and drop your belly towards the floor meanwhile lift your chin and chest upwards. Then release top of your feet to the floor, exhale and round your back dropping your head and tailbone down and pulling your belly inwards and drop your head. Hold the stretch the get back to starting position.
correctForm:
Inhale and exhale respectively during cat moves
Don’t overuse your lower back muscles

name: abductor_stretch_left.gif
info: Abductor stretch is an exercise that primarily targets abductor muscles and thigh muscles.
howTo: Stand straight, put both hands on your side hips and spread your feets wider than your shoulders. Take left foot step forward and start bending your upper body weight towards that left side along with bending knee. Hold the stretch, then come to starting position and repeat on the other side.
correctForm:
Stabilize body weight on top of the leg
Squeeze your abs and glutes to stabilize your body

name: abductor_stretch_right.gif
info: Abductor stretch is an exercise that primarily targets abductor muscles and thigh muscles.
howTo: Stand straight, put both hands on your side hips and spread your feets wider than your shoulders. Take left foot step forward and start bending your upper body weight towards that left side along with bending knee. Hold the stretch, then come to starting position and repeat on the other side.
correctForm:
Stabilize body weight on top of the leg
Squeeze your abs and glutes to stabilize your body

name: pelvic_stretch1.gif
info: Pelvic stretch is an effective exercise that primarily targets pelvic muscles, glutes and thigh muscles.
howTo: Stand straight and lift your right leg with bended knee, grab knee with your both hands and pull towards torso. Hold the stretch then repeat with left leg.
correctForm:
Stabilize body weight on one leg
Take deep breaths while stretching

name: quad_stretch1.gif
info: Quadricep stretch is an effective exercise that mainly targets your quads, hip flexors and ankles.
howTo: Stand straight and shift your body weight to the left leg. Lift up your right foot, grasp it with your right hand from backside and feel the stretch in your quads by pulling it towards the hip. Hold the stretch then repeat with right leg.
correctForm:
Take deep breaths while stretching
Grab the top of your foot with respective hand

name: neck_stretch1.gif
info: Neck stretch is an effective exercise that treats neck and shoulder muscles.
howTo: Stand straight with your feet shoulder width apart, tilt your head towards shoulder. Place hand on your head and gently pull until you feel the stretch. Hold the stretch then repeat on the other side.
correctForm:
Relax your neck, arm & shoulders
Exhale as you stretch muscles, inhale as you release the stretch

name: tricep_stretch1.gif
info: Tricep stretch is a great way to improve your upper body’s flexibility and strengthen shoulders.
howTo: Stand straight with your feet shoulder width apart, raise and bend one arm so your hand is in the middle of upper back. Grasp your elbow with the other hand and pull gently to feel stretch in tricep. Hold the stretch then repeat on the other side.
correctForm:
Keep your neck & shoulders relaxed
Exhale as you stretch, inhale as you release the stretch

name: hamstring_stretch.gif
info: Shoulder and back stretch is an effective exercise that treats your lower back pain and leg pain.
howTo: Stand straight and extend right leg out in front of you in a position where foot heel is on the floor and toe towards the roof. Bend your back leg knee while supporting the knee with both palms. Slowly put weight on back leg knee while straightening your front leg until a stretch is felt in the hamstrings. Hold the stretch then repeat with left leg.
correctForm:
Keep your knees straight while stretching leg
Keep your lower back and hips flat

name: downward_upward_dog.gif
info: Downward upward dog is an exercise that primarily targets your back, hamstrings, chest and shoulders.
howTo: Start in a plank position with shoulders on the top of your wrists, heels on top of the balls of feet and place feets at shoulders width apart. Lift your hips up without moving your hands or feet that makes downward facing dog pose. Then drive your hips forward towards the floor in a position with pelvis go down towards the floor. Place your hands underneath your shoulders with chest lift and maintain a comfortable height of torso that makes upward facing dog pose.
correctForm:
Maintain your wrists and elbows straight
Open your shoulders and remove all stress from neck

name: lunge_stretch.gif
info: Lunge stretch is an exercise than primarily targets abs, glutes, quads and hamstrings.
howTo: Stand straight, take a step forward then slowly bend both knees until your back knee touches the floor. Stand back up and repeat the motion with alternative leg.
correctForm:
While bending front knee, make 90 degree angle from thigh to leg
Maintain your feet hip width apart

name: diagonal_squat_left.gif
howTo: Stand on one leg.Bend your leg to 45 degrees.Reach your right arm diagonally across your body towards the left side of your knee.Return to center.Reach your left arm diagonally across your body towards the right side of your knee.

name: diagonal_squat_right.gif
howTo: Stand on one leg.Bend your leg to 45 degrees.Reach your right arm diagonally across your body towards the left side of your knee.Return to center.Reach your left arm diagonally across your body towards the right side of your knee.

name: elevated_split_squat_left.gif
howTo: Begin by placing the top of your right foot on the bench, with your left leg straight. Bend your left knee, engage your right glute, and lower your pelvis toward the ground.Straighten your left leg and rise back up to the starting position. Complete three sets of 10-15 reps on each leg.

name: elevated_split_squat_right.gif
howTo: Begin by placing the top of your left foot on the bench, with your right leg straight. Bend your right knee, engage your left glute, and lower your pelvis toward the ground.Straighten your right leg and rise back up to the starting position. Complete three sets of 10-15 reps on each leg.
